{title: When I Take My Vacation In Heaven}
{artist: Johnny Cash}
{composer: Written by Herbert Buffum and R.E. Winsett}

[3/4 time]
[C]There are those who are taking vacations
To the [F]mountains the lakes and the [C]sea
Where they rest from their cares and their troubles
What a [D7]wonderful time that must [G7]be
But it [C]seems not my [G7]lot to be like [C]them
I must [F]toil through the heat and the [C]cold
Seeking out the lost sheep on a mountain
Bringing [D7]wanderers [G7]back to the [C]fold
But when I take my vacation in heaven
What a [F]wonderful time that will [C]be
Hearing concerts by the heavenly chorus
And the [D7]face of my Savior I'll [G7]see
Sitting [C]down on the [G7]banks of the [C]river
Neath the [F]shade of the evergreen [C]tree
There I'll rest from my burdens forever
Won't you [D7]take your [G7]vacation with [C]me
Repeat #4